ft-bzl implements syntax-based folding support.

Before demonstrating how it works, this file needs to source the setupvroom.vim
file, which bootstraps the ft-bzl plugin and configures it to work properly
under vroom. It also defines the CheckEq helper.

  :source $VROOMDIR/setupvroom.vim

You can enable automatic folding for BUILD files by defining g:ft_bzl_fold = 1.

  :let g:ft_bzl_fold = 1

Folding relies on syntax to detect folds, and filetype plugin to enable them.

  :syntax on
  :filetype plugin on

With folding enabled, this cc_library rule can be collapsed to a fold line with
nice fold text like this: cc_library( "foo" )  10 lines

  :silent file BUILD
  :set filetype=bzl
  % cc_library(<CR>
  |    name = "foo",<CR>
  |    srcs = [<CR>
  |        "foo.cc",<CR>
  |        "foo-impl.h",<CR>
  |    ],<CR>
  |    hdrs = ["foo.h"],<CR>
  |    deps = [<CR>
  |    ],<CR>
  |)
  :%foldclose
  :call CheckEq(len(foldtextresult(1)), winwidth(0))
  :echomsg foldtextresult(1)
  ~ cc_library\( "foo" \)\s+10 lines (regex)

There will also be inner folds defined for the srcs and deps sections.

  :%foldopen
  :3,6foldclose
  :call CheckEq(len(foldtextresult(3)), winwidth(0))
  :echomsg foldtextresult(3)
  ~     srcs = \[ ... \],\s+4 lines (regex)
  :%foldopen
  :8,9foldclose
  :call CheckEq(len(foldtextresult(8)), winwidth(0))
  :echomsg foldtextresult(8)
  ~     deps = \[  \],\s+2 lines (regex)
